//GAME PROJECT
//USER STORIES
//As a player, I want to land on a clear start screen so I know what the game is and how to begin.
//As a player, I want to quickly see or understand how to move and shoot so I can start playing without confusion
//As a player, I want the main game area to appear with the character, the enemies, and my
//score/lives visible so I know what’s happening right away.
//As a player, I want to move left and right smoothly so I can position myself where I need to be.
//As a player, I want to press a key to shoot so I can try to clear enemies before they reach me
//As a player, I want to see enemies moving toward me in predictable patterns so I can plan how to avoid losing lives.
//As a player, I want a small visual or/and score update when I hit an enemy so I feel rewarded
//As a player, I want to clearly see when enemies shoot at me so I have a chance to dodge.
//As a player, I want to lose a life  when an enemy reaches the bottom/ or an enemy bullet hits my character so the game play continues.
//As a player, I want my score and lives displayed at all times so I can track how well I’m doing
//As a player, I want the game to acknowledge when I clear all enemies in a wave so I know I’m moving forward
//As a player, I want a clear Game Over message when I run out of lives so I know the round has ended
//As a player, I want a quick way to restart the game so I can try again right away.

//MORE
//As a player, I want different types of enemies (speed, movement, shooting) so the game doesn’t feel repetitive
//As a player, I want a way to pause the game if needed


